 Uitenhage -  Police are investigating a case of hijacking after three men allegedly targeted a courier van in KwaNobuhle, Uitenhage on Monday. "On Monday, at about 16:15, a driver of a courier service van alleged that he stopped at Mgolodela Street, KwaNobuhle (Uitenhage) with his assistant to deliver a parcel," said police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "He further said that three men accosted them and one of the suspects had a firearm in his hand and demanded the vehicle’s keys. "The three men then jumped into the van and sped off." Moments later, police recovered the courier van abandoned in an open field with no parcels inside near Philemon Kona Street, KwaNobuhle. "It was also said that there were about 36 parcels inside the van that were awaiting delivery," Sgt Nkohli said. "Police are following all leads and anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of suspects is urged to contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer Deon Arnolds at 082 779 7277 or Crime Stop 08600 10111. "All callers may remain anonymous and all information will be treated strictly confidential." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 